</html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uxexysblackwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xexys Blackwind</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=ftp://imagesrv:imagesrv@65.2.198.6:5150/xbutton.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/01 8:35:22 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=ftp://imagesrv:imagesrv@65.2.198.6:5150/xexys60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hunting at 40??</span><hr size=1> Sol B is the devil.<br>
<br>
Whenever I go there with ANY of my characters, it usually ends in me dragging corpses out of the sonic bat room. <p><a href="http://eqforge.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=3982" target="blank">Xexys Blackwind</a><BR>
Half Elven Warrior of Tunare<br>
Servant of The Tribunal<br>
<center>
<br><img src="ftp://imagesrv:imagesrv@65.2.198.6:5150/Xexys-sig.jpg">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ulyriel2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lyriel2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/01 10:13:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hunting at 40??</span><hr size=1> Xexys,<br>
<br>
   I love Sol B, can't get enough of it.  When one of your critters hits 35 to window room until 37 or 38, higher if you're not well equipped.  Just a 5 second run up that one hall and you're in Sol A, safe and sound.  As your level and equipment allows, move into KPC.  Make sure your group is a sound one and rock on for 8 hours at a stretch, lots of mith for everyone.  Bats and bugs are fine if you're at the proper level.  I had my druid (52), a 52 warrior and 55 shammie in their the other day.  4 hours straight, lots of GSD's, black chitin legs, and one chitin bracer.  <br>
<br>
Of course there's tons of places to play, but for the appropriate level, Sol B experience is hard to beat. <p><html>
